# Chapter 6 — Liberation (Pemakö, Tibet)

*Keeper-facing summary of Chapter 6 of The Children of Fear. Structure lives in
the sibling `.arc`, stat blocks in the `.actor`, campaign lore in
`children-of-fear-0.4-campaign-overview.lore`. Consult your copy of the campaign
for full text, read-aloud passages, and handouts. First chapter of the linear
Climax phase (see the campaign `FLOW`).*

## Role in the campaign

With the three Gathering components in hand, the campaign turns toward its climax.
Chapter 6 leads the party deep into the **hidden land of Pemakö** — a legendary
*beyul* (sacred hidden valley) in the remote gorges of southeastern Tibet — in
search of a goddess site central to the endgame ("Where the Goddess Lies"). It is
a wilderness-and-wonder chapter with rising cosmic horror.

## Setting

**Pemakö** — a semi-mythical hidden land, its discovery attributed to lamas such
as **Jatsun Nyingpo** and his disciple **Rigdzin Duddul Dorje**, wreathed in
Buddhist prophecy (e.g. the 75 hidden waterfalls said to lie along a stretch of
the upper gorge). A **disputed border** and near-impassable terrain make it one of
the least-accessible places on Earth.

## Structure and key beats

**The Lotus Displayed / Hidden Gems.** Background on Pemakö as a hidden Pure Land
and its prophetic geography.

**Set Up — Where the Goddess Lies.** The objective: reach the goddess site hidden
in the gorge's waterfalls.

**The Plant Hunter.** A Western botanist/plant-hunter NPC operating in the region —
a mundane companion or complication for the trek.

**Aping the Mi-Go.** The **Mi-Go** (fungi from Yuggoth) are active here, shadowing
and mimicking; the chapter's principal Mythos threat, tied to the strange
vibrations/storms the party has felt.

**Hazards of the deep valley.** Datura / thorn-apple (which penalises perception
and mental rolls), and horrors such as **glaciers built from stacked skeletons** —
escalating body-horror as the party nears the goddess.

## Key NPCs & threats

- **The Plant Hunter** — a Western botanist in Pemakö.
- **The Mi-Go** — the alien intelligences stalking and aping the investigators.
  (Stat blocks in the `.actor`.)
- **Tenzin Kalsang / the Tokabhaya** — the lama's goal drives the descent; the
  antagonists close in as the climax nears.

## Clues & handouts (as information)

- Chapter handouts and the regional *What Your Investigator Knows* material for
  Tibet / the hidden lands.

## Keeper guidance

- Play Pemakö as awe and dread — a place out of legend that punishes trespass.
- Use the datura and skeleton-glacier horrors to ratchet Sanity pressure into the
  climax.

## Transition

Chapter 6 delivers the party to the threshold of the endgame; the Climax continues
into Chapter 7 (*Spirits of the Earth*) — the ritual site.
